{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012zPX7Dbe1nBDXbRY1LXVkC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The certificate has SANs:\n- `DNS:localhost`\n- `DNS:*.elasticsearch.svc`\n- `DNS:*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n\nThis is great! The wildcard `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` will match the headless service pod DNS names like `elasticsearch-0.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` - wait, actually no. The wildcard `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` would match `es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` but not `elasticsearch-0.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`.\nThe `*.elasticsearch.svc` wildcard does cover the service names like `es-headless.elasticsearch.svc` and `es-http.elasticsearch.svc`, but for transport between nodes using their full headless DNS names like `elasticsearch-0.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`, the wildcard doesn't apply since it's looking at a deeper subdomain level. So for transport SSL, I should probably use `verification_mode: certificate` to validate the cert is properly signed without strict hostname matching.\n\nNow I'm setting up the actual Kubernetes manifests—I'll need a ConfigMap for the Elasticsearch configuration, a headless Service for node discovery, an HTTP Service for client access, and a StatefulSet with three replicas. Since this is a single-node cluster, I'll need to add tolerations for the control plane taint and skip the anti-affinity rules that would prevent scheduling.\n\nI also need to handle the `vm.max_map_count` sysctl requirement with a privileged init container before Elasticsearch starts.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":906,"cache_read_input_tokens":30500,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":906},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed9fce89-0c75-4744-822d-7cd7259fdcfc","uuid":"a06ef378-118e-40d3-88e8-141feec5b313","request_id":"req_011Ccf2ZWDmtWNnVmUFyTUvn"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012zPX7Dbe1nBDXbRY1LXVkC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cert covers `*.elasticsearch.svc` and `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` — good for HTTP but transport node-to-node names won't match. I'll use `verification_mode: certificate` for transport. Now deploying all resources."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":906,"cache_read_input_tokens":30500,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":906},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed9fce89-0c75-4744-822d-7cd7259fdcfc","uuid":"8f67492c-cd59-47cf-a019-31ec4d26ca6b","request_id":"req_011Ccf2ZWDmtWNnVmUFyTUvn"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012zPX7Dbe1nBDXbRY1LXVkC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JQTEisWg8a7c81DZEEwzd9","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/short/r7/elasticsearch-data-path-health-drill-20260703_111410/stages/stage_01/es-deploy.yaml","content":"---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  elasticsearch.yml: |\n    cluster.name: es-cluster\n    node.name: ${HOSTNAME}\n    network.host: 0.0.0.0\n    http.port: 9200\n    transport.port: 9300\n\n    discovery.seed_hosts:\n      - es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\n    cluster.initial_master_nodes:\n      - elasticsearch-0\n      - elasticsearch-1\n      - elasticsearch-2\n\n    xpack.security.enabled: true\n\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-headless\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  clusterIP: None\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: http\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n    - name: transport\n      port: 9300\n      targetPort: 9300\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-http\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  type: ClusterIP\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: https\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n---\napiVersion: policy/v1\nkind: PodDisruptionBudget\nmetadata:\n  name: es-pdb\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  minAvailable: 2\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n---\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: StatefulSet\nmetadata:\n  name: elasticsearch\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  serviceName: es-headless\n  replicas: 3\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: elasticsearch\n    spec:\n      tolerations:\n        - key: node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane\n          operator: Exists\n          effect: NoSchedule\n        - key: node-role.kubernetes.io/master\n          operator: Exists\n          effect: NoSchedule\n      initContainers:\n        - name: fix-permissions\n          image: busybox:1.35\n          command: [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"chown -R 1000:1000 /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\"]\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n        - name: increase-vm-max-map\n          image: busybox:1.35\n          command: [\"sysctl\", \"-w\", \"vm.max_map_count=262144\"]\n          securityContext:\n            privileged: true\n      containers:\n        - name: elasticsearch\n          image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.0\n          ports:\n            - containerPort: 9200\n              name: http\n            - containerPort: 9300\n              name: transport\n          env:\n            - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n              valueFrom:\n                secretKeyRef:\n                  name: elastic-password\n                  key: password\n            - name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n              value: \"-Xms512m -Xmx512m\"\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: config\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml\n              subPath: elasticsearch.yml\n            - name: certs\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n              readOnly: true\n            - name: data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n          readinessProbe:\n            exec:\n              command:\n                - sh\n                - -c\n                - |\n                  curl -sf --cacert /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt \\\n                    -u elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD} \\\n                    https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health?wait_for_status=yellow&timeout=5s\n            initialDelaySeconds: 30\n            periodSeconds: 10\n            timeoutSeconds: 10\n            failureThreshold: 6\n          resources:\n            requests:\n              memory: \"1Gi\"\n              cpu: \"500m\"\n            limits:\n              memory: \"2Gi\"\n              cpu: \"2\"\n      volumes:\n        - name: config\n          configMap:\n            name: es-config\n        - name: certs\n          secret:\n            secretName: es-http-tls\n  volumeClaimTemplates:\n    - metadata:\n        name: data\n      spec:\n        accessModes: [\"ReadWriteOnce\"]\n        resources:\n          requests:\n            storage: 5Gi\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":906,"cache_read_input_tokens":30500,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":906},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed9fce89-0c75-4744-822d-7cd7259fdcfc","uuid":"183cb031-429e-4164-a01b-30e9fe354a25","request_id":"req_011Ccf2ZWDmtWNnVmUFyTUvn"}
